{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":747,"text":"The year is 1800."},{"time":3070,"text":"A curious little invention is being talked about."},{"time":6126,"text":"It's called a microscope."},{"time":9207,"text":"What it allows you to do"},{"time":10986,"text":"is see tiny little lifeforms"},{"time":13628,"text":"that are invisible to the naked eye."},{"time":16115,"text":"Soon comes the medical discovery"},{"time":18143,"text":"that many of these lifeforms are actually causes"},{"time":21228,"text":"of terrible human diseases."},{"time":23419,"text":"Imagine what happened to the society"},{"time":26204,"text":"when they realized"},{"time":28192,"text":"that an English mom in her teacup"},{"time":31008,"text":"actually was drinking a monster soup,"},{"time":34144,"text":"not very far from here. This is from London."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37293,"text":"Fast forward 200 years."},{"time":40135,"text":"We still have this monster soup around,"},{"time":42267,"text":"and it's taken hold in the developing countries"},{"time":45122,"text":"around the tropical belt."},{"time":47538,"text":"Just for malaria itself,"},{"time":50101,"text":"there are a million deaths a year,"},{"time":52546,"text":"and more than a billion people"},{"time":54292,"text":"that need to be tested because they are at risk"},{"time":56940,"text":"for different species of malarial infections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60175,"text":"Now it's actually very simple to put a face"},{"time":62986,"text":"to many of these monsters."},{"time":64781,"text":"You take a stain, like acridine orange"},{"time":67408,"text":"or a fluorescent stain or Giemsa,"},{"time":69525,"text":"and a microscope, and you look at them."},{"time":72638,"text":"They all have faces."},{"time":75018,"text":"Why is that so, that Alex in Kenya,"},{"time":77656,"text":"Fatima in Bangladesh, Navjoot in Mumbai,"},{"time":80884,"text":"and Julie and Mary in Uganda still wait months"},{"time":84305,"text":"to be able to diagnose why they are sick?"},{"time":87884,"text":"And that's primarily because scalability"},{"time":90910,"text":"of the diagnostics is completely out of reach."},{"time":93942,"text":"And remember that number: one billion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97858,"text":"The problem lies with the microscope itself."},{"time":101759,"text":"Even though the pinnacle of modern science,"},{"time":104135,"text":"research microscopes are\nnot designed for field testing."},{"time":107270,"text":"Neither were they first designed"},{"time":108950,"text":"for diagnostics at all."},{"time":111101,"text":"They are heavy, bulky, really hard to maintain,"},{"time":114489,"text":"and cost a lot of money."},{"time":116790,"text":"This picture is Mahatma Gandhi in the '40s"},{"time":120195,"text":"using the exact same setup\nthat we actually use today"},{"time":123489,"text":"for diagnosing T.B. in his ashram"},{"time":126173,"text":"in Sevagram in India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128618,"text":"Two of my students, Jim and James,"},{"time":131945,"text":"traveled around India and Thailand,"},{"time":134265,"text":"starting to think about this problem a lot."},{"time":136517,"text":"We saw all kinds of donated equipment."},{"time":138992,"text":"We saw fungus growing on microscope lenses."},{"time":141904,"text":"And we saw people who had a functional microscope"},{"time":144099,"text":"but just didn't know how to even turn it on."},{"time":147050,"text":"What grew out of that work and that trip"},{"time":149690,"text":"was actually the idea of what we call Foldscopes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153441,"text":"So what is a Foldscope?"},{"time":155264,"text":"A Foldscope is a completely functional microscope,"},{"time":158813,"text":"a platform for fluorescence, bright-field,"},{"time":161943,"text":"polarization, projection,"},{"time":163518,"text":"all kinds of advanced microscopy"},{"time":166086,"text":"built purely by folding paper."},{"time":169301,"text":"So, now you think, how is that possible?"},{"time":172162,"text":"I'm going to show you some examples here,"},{"time":174125,"text":"and we will run through some of them."},{"time":175926,"text":"It starts with a single sheet of paper."},{"time":179710,"text":"What you see here is all the possible components"},{"time":183081,"text":"to build a functional bright-field\nand fluorescence microscope."},{"time":187506,"text":"So, there are three stages:"},{"time":189315,"text":"There is the optical stage, the illumination stage"},{"time":192064,"text":"and the mask-holding stage."},{"time":194532,"text":"And there are micro optics at the bottom"},{"time":196404,"text":"that's actually embedded in the paper itself."},{"time":199278,"text":"What you do is, you take it on,"},{"time":201782,"text":"and just like you are playing like a toy,"},{"time":204558,"text":"which it is,"},{"time":208584,"text":"I tab it off,"},{"time":215039,"text":"and I break it off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217221,"text":"This paper has no instructions and no languages."},{"time":219945,"text":"There is a code, a color code embedded,"},{"time":222264,"text":"that tells you exactly how to\nfold that specific microscope."},{"time":226875,"text":"When it's done, it looks something like this,"},{"time":229524,"text":"has all the functionalities of a standard microscope,"},{"time":232255,"text":"just like an XY stage,"},{"time":234136,"text":"a place where a sample slide could go,"},{"time":238557,"text":"for example right here."},{"time":241097,"text":"We didn't want to change this,"},{"time":242609,"text":"because this is the standard"},{"time":243981,"text":"that's been optimized for over the years,"},{"time":245834,"text":"and many health workers are actually used to this."},{"time":248530,"text":"So this is what changes,"},{"time":249991,"text":"but the standard stains all remain the same"},{"time":252158,"text":"for many different diseases."},{"time":253933,"text":"You pop this in."},{"time":256865,"text":"There is an XY stage,"},{"time":260751,"text":"and then there is a focusing stage,"},{"time":262724,"text":"which is a flexure mechanism"},{"time":264590,"text":"that's built in paper itself that allows us to move"},{"time":267143,"text":"and focus the lenses by micron steps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270124,"text":"So what's really interesting about this object,"},{"time":272257,"text":"and my students hate when I do this,"},{"time":274140,"text":"but I'm going to do this anyway,"},{"time":275901,"text":"is these are rugged devices."},{"time":277857,"text":"I can turn it on and throw it on the floor"},{"time":282434,"text":"and really try to stomp on it."},{"time":285386,"text":"And they last, even though they're designed"},{"time":287761,"text":"from a very flexible material, like paper."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291224,"text":"Another fun fact is, this is what we actually"},{"time":294076,"text":"send out there as a standard diagnostic tool,"},{"time":298131,"text":"but here in this envelope"},{"time":299900,"text":"I have 30 different foldscopes"},{"time":302291,"text":"of different configurations all in a single folder."},{"time":308022,"text":"And I'm going to pick one randomly."},{"time":309834,"text":"This one, it turns out, is actually designed"},{"time":311916,"text":"specifically for malaria,"},{"time":313479,"text":"because it has the fluorescent filters built"},{"time":315790,"text":"specifically for diagnosing malaria."},{"time":317887,"text":"So the idea of very specific diagnostic microscopes"},{"time":321815,"text":"comes out of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323581,"text":"So up till now, you didn't actually see"},{"time":326520,"text":"what I would see from one of these setups."},{"time":329477,"text":"So what I would like to do is,"},{"time":331158,"text":"if we could dim the lights, please,"},{"time":332784,"text":"it turns out foldscopes are\nalso projection microscopes."},{"time":336449,"text":"I have these two microscopes that I'm going to turn --"},{"time":338983,"text":"go to the back of the wall --"},{"time":340736,"text":"and just project, and this way you will see"},{"time":342444,"text":"exactly what I would see."},{"time":344564,"text":"What you're looking at --"},{"time":346350,"text":"(Applause) —"},{"time":348733,"text":"This is a cross-section of a compound eye,"},{"time":351369,"text":"and when I'm going to zoom in closer, right there,"},{"time":353720,"text":"I am going through the z-axis."},{"time":355964,"text":"You actually see how the lenses are cut together"},{"time":358988,"text":"in the cross-section pattern."},{"time":360561,"text":"Another example, one of my favorite insects,"},{"time":363117,"text":"I love to hate this one,"},{"time":365094,"text":"is a mosquito,"},{"time":366875,"text":"and you're seeing the antenna of a culex pipiens."},{"time":370637,"text":"Right there."},{"time":374000,"text":"All from the simple setup that I actually described."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378213,"text":"So my wife has been field testing"},{"time":379986,"text":"some of our microscopes"},{"time":381986,"text":"by washing my clothes whenever I forget them"},{"time":384467,"text":"in the dryer."},{"time":386496,"text":"So it turns out they're waterproof, and --"},{"time":389296,"text":"(Laughter) —"},{"time":391084,"text":"right here is just fluorescent water,"},{"time":393582,"text":"and I don't know if you can actually see this."},{"time":395132,"text":"This also shows you how \nthe projection scope works."},{"time":397521,"text":"You get to see the beam the \nway it's projected and bent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404199,"text":"Can we get the lights back on again?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407139,"text":"So I'm quickly going to show you,"},{"time":408926,"text":"since I'm running out of time,"},{"time":410975,"text":"in terms of how much it costs for us to manufacture,"},{"time":413401,"text":"the biggest idea was roll-to-roll manufacturing,"},{"time":416481,"text":"so we built this out of 50 cents of parts and costs."},{"time":419603,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":422462,"text":"And what this allows us to do"},{"time":424557,"text":"is to think about a new paradigm in microscopy,"},{"time":426893,"text":"which we call use-and-throw microscopy."},{"time":428910,"text":"I'm going to give you a quick snapshot"},{"time":430999,"text":"of some of the parts that go in."},{"time":432762,"text":"Here is a sheet of paper."},{"time":434221,"text":"This is when we were thinking about the idea."},{"time":436310,"text":"This is an A4 sheet of paper."},{"time":437665,"text":"These are the three stages that you actually see."},{"time":439646,"text":"And the optical components, if you\nlook at the inset up on the right,"},{"time":443076,"text":"we had to figure out a way to manufacture lenses"},{"time":445503,"text":"in paper itself at really high throughputs,"},{"time":447815,"text":"so it uses a process of self-assembly"},{"time":449674,"text":"and surface tension"},{"time":450786,"text":"to build achromatic lenses in the paper itself."},{"time":454322,"text":"So that's where the lenses go."},{"time":455767,"text":"There are some light sources."},{"time":457379,"text":"And essentially, in the end,"},{"time":458764,"text":"all the parts line up because of origami,"},{"time":461942,"text":"because of the fact that origami allows us"},{"time":465213,"text":"micron-scale precision of optical alignment."},{"time":468193,"text":"So even though this looks like a simple toy,"},{"time":470822,"text":"the aspects of engineering that go in"},{"time":472736,"text":"something like this are fairly sophisticated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475422,"text":"So here is another obvious thing that we would do,"},{"time":478657,"text":"typically, if I was going to show"},{"time":480250,"text":"that these microscopes are robust,"},{"time":481755,"text":"is go to the third floor and\ndrop it from the floor itself."},{"time":485593,"text":"There it is, and it survives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488916,"text":"So for us, the next step actually"},{"time":491093,"text":"is really finishing our field trials."},{"time":492932,"text":"We are starting at the end of the summer."},{"time":495037,"text":"We are at a stage where we'll be \nmaking thousands of microscopes."},{"time":497964,"text":"That would be the first time where we would be"},{"time":500108,"text":"doing field trials with the highest density"},{"time":502193,"text":"of microscopes ever at a given place."},{"time":504748,"text":"We've started collecting data for malaria,"},{"time":506828,"text":"Chagas disease and giardia from patients themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510624,"text":"And I want to leave you with this picture."},{"time":512718,"text":"I had not anticipated this before,"},{"time":514643,"text":"but a really interesting link"},{"time":516330,"text":"between hands-on science education"},{"time":518225,"text":"and global health."},{"time":519483,"text":"What are the tools that we're actually providing"},{"time":522409,"text":"the kids who are going to fight"},{"time":524589,"text":"this monster soup for tomorrow?"},{"time":526507,"text":"I would love for them to be able to just print out"},{"time":528865,"text":"a Foldscope and carry them around in their pockets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530994,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533900,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}